cudéry) über Autoren wie Bohse und Hunold bis zu Weiterführungen bei Christoph Martin Wieland. So entsteht ein Gesamtbild des „romanesken Erzählens“ im 18. Jahrhundert.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aGerman fictionyEarly modern, 1500-1700xHistory and criticism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh  aDiscourse of Gallantry.  aHistory of the novel.  aLiterature around 1700.  aRules for good conduct.  aWieland, Christoph Martin.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Literary and Cultural Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110637854oZDB-23-GLC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2007z9783110277135oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET LINGUISTIK UND LITERATURWISSENSCHAFT  2007z9783110276909oZDB-23-DGA0 cprintz978348436625140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311093740440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110937404423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110937404/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGAb2007  aZDB-23-DGGb2007  aZDB-23-GLCc2000d2014